Title: Debate Summary Evaluation 1
Description: Help us compare different summaries of online debates
Answer.abortion-plain_v_stock-comment: B comprises a number of random comments that might have been made by someone who opposes legal abortion, but a significant number don't seem to conform to any position, and are just uses of fallacy. A seems to have a clearer thread of reasoning that ties most of the points together and uses them to support one another, but ultimately relies on fallacy to support the argument.
Answer.creation-layout_v_formatted-comme: They are essentially identical in content and format, save for the bolding and coloring, which make the piece ridiculous to read because of the natural emphasis, which is unnecessary.
Answer.creation-layout_v_stock-comment: A is a bunch of statements that might have been made in a debate, but generally seems to be hand waving about various points. B doesn't really make any clear and supported points in spite of its superior organization.
